main event: A farmer reported unusual material that was analyzed and identified as phosphorescent glass, originating potentially from manufactured items.
interesting points: The material was observed on October 25, 1962, in Corpus Christi, Texas., The course of the object was reported to be zig-zag., The analysis indicated the glass was produced by the Illinois Glass company., The sample exhibited unique characteristics not found in commonly available glass., Further tests showed no radioactivity in the sample.
sighted object: a piece of unusual material (phosphorescent glass)
witness description: Observers included ground-visual and ground-radar personnel.
